            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA">
                <p>Sacred to Mercury Augustus. Valerius Valens, standard-bearer [of the legion 13 Gemina], and Domitius Zosimus, financial agent(?) for the accounts of Domitius Terentianus, having been warned, restored [the temple?], when Peregrinus and Aemilianus were consuls.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The same Valerius Valens and Domitius Zosimus are mentioned in AE 1991.778.</p> 
            </div>
